# RSS Dashboard (local fork)

The bundled `main.js` under `.obsidian/plugins/rss-dashboard/` is patched (not from the marketplace alone). When editing or re-applying after plugin updates:

1. **External links**: Replace `window.open(url, "_blank")` with `window.open(url, "rss-dashboard-external")` so the browser reuses one named window/tab instead of opening a new tab every time (YouTube button, Open in Browser, context menus, feed preview).

2. **Reader pane**: `openArticleInNewTab` uses `workspace.getLeaf("tab")` (not `"split"` on desktop) so the article reader opens as a new tab in the current tab group instead of a new split.

3. **Do not change** `window.open(s, "_blank")` for the blob/XML export flow.

Re-apply these edits if the plugin auto-updates and overwrites `main.js`.
